WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:03.003
-GIRL HELP!

00:06.136 --> 00:07.746
HELP!

00:11.968 --> 00:13.448
HELP ME!

00:20.150 --> 00:21.630
HELP!

00:26.939 --> 00:27.853
[CHOKING]

00:35.252 --> 00:36.384
HELP!

01:00.364 --> 01:01.626
[GRUNTS]

01:06.457 --> 01:08.503
-NO PULSE, SHE'S NOT
BREATHING, BEGIN CPR!

01:12.550 --> 01:15.336
-ONE, TWO
THREE FOUR, FIVE,

01:15.466 --> 01:18.252
SIX, SEVEN,
EIGHT, NINE, TEN,

01:18.861 --> 01:21.516
11, 12, 13, 14, 15

01:23.387 --> 01:25.520
IS SHE ALIVE?

01:26.042 --> 01:29.001
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

01:34.050 --> 01:37.575
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

01:37.706 --> 01:41.492
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

01:42.058 --> 01:45.453
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

01:45.583 --> 01:49.196
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

01:49.326 --> 01:51.676
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

01:52.329 --> 01:54.288
♪IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT ♪

01:57.856 --> 01:59.728
♪ CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:59.858 --> 02:03.210
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

02:06.691 --> 02:10.173
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

02:10.304 --> 02:14.525
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR,
NO DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

02:14.656 --> 02:17.659
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:17.789 --> 02:20.401
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

02:20.966 --> 02:23.621
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:34.415 --> 02:36.678
FIFTEEN, IS SHE ALIVE?

02:37.896 --> 02:39.376
STILL NO PULSE,
STILL NOT BREATHING.

02:40.247 --> 02:41.117
CONTINUE CPR.

02:45.513 --> 02:48.690
ONE, TWO
THREE, FOUR, FIVE,

02:48.820 --> 02:51.127
SIX, SEVEN,
EIGHT, NINE, TEN,

02:51.258 --> 02:54.826
11, 12, 13, 14, 15.

02:55.740 --> 02:56.959
IS SHE ALIVE?

02:57.089 --> 02:58.134
-KIDS: YES!

03:02.007 --> 03:03.357
[LAUGHS]

03:04.836 --> 03:07.012
-MITCH: GOOD JOB, STEPHANIE,
GOOD JOB.

03:07.143 --> 03:08.971
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN UP.

03:09.101 --> 03:12.322
DID WE DO THE PROPER
PROCEDURE FOR TWO-MAN CPR?

03:12.801 --> 03:14.063
-KIDS: NO!

03:14.194 --> 03:17.066
-WHAT IS THE PROPER
PROCEDURE FOR TWO-MAN CPR?

03:17.197 --> 03:18.589
KIDS: FIVE TO ONE.

03:18.937 --> 03:21.244
WHAT'S THE PROPER
PROCEDURE FOR ONE-MAN CPR?

03:21.375 --> 03:23.333
-KIDS: 15 TO TWO.

03:24.508 --> 03:25.857
SHOW ME.

03:25.988 --> 03:28.077
THAT'S RIGHT,
TILT THE HEAD BACK.

03:28.556 --> 03:30.645
LOOK, LISTEN,
AND FEEL FOR BREATHING.

03:31.733 --> 03:33.387
CHECK THE CAROTID ARTERY
FOR PULSE.

03:34.431 --> 03:37.478
OKAY, BEGIN ONE-MAN CPR.

03:37.608 --> 03:38.870
TWO BREATHS,

03:41.133 --> 03:44.702
KIDS: ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX...

03:44.833 --> 03:45.964
-MITCH: SLOW DOWN!

03:46.095 --> 03:48.793
[KIDS COUNTING]

03:50.230 --> 03:51.448
-MITCH: TWO BREATHS, GOOD.

03:56.236 --> 04:01.415
-ONE...
-[KIDS COUNTING]

04:06.158 --> 04:08.204
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT, GIVE
YOURSELVES A ROUND OF APPLAUSE.

04:08.335 --> 04:10.989
GOOD JOB, GOOD JOB, YEE-HAH!

04:11.120 --> 04:13.253
YOU GUYS MUST HAVE
PRETTY AWESOME TEACHERS.

04:14.428 --> 04:15.907
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT,
WE'LL SEE YOU NEXT WEEK

04:16.038 --> 04:17.560
FOR WATER SAFETY, ALL RIGHT?

04:21.348 --> 04:22.653
-HEY, YOU GUYS.
-HEY.

04:22.784 --> 04:24.655
-I APPRECIATE YOU LETTING
TIMMY HANG OUT WITH YOU.

04:25.221 --> 04:26.570
-INTERESTING KID.

04:26.875 --> 04:28.616
WONDER WHAT'S GOING ON
INSIDE THAT MIND.

04:29.094 --> 04:31.227
THINK HE UNDERSTOOD ANYTHING
ABOUT WHAT WE JUST DID?

04:31.358 --> 04:33.795
WELL, IT'S HARD TO TELL
WITH AN AUTISTIC CHILD.

04:33.925 --> 04:35.579
ESPECIALLY ONE WHO DOESN'T TALK.

04:36.058 --> 04:38.582
FACT IS MOST AUTISTIC KIDS
DON'T TALK.

04:39.453 --> 04:43.152
THEY COMMUNICATE WITH GESTURES,
MOTIONS, THEIR EYES.

04:43.283 --> 04:44.936
IT'S ALMOST LIKE THEY
LIVE IN ANOTHER WORLD.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.025
I DON'T KNOW
HOW MY SISTER DEALS WITH IT.

04:47.635 --> 04:50.377
I THINK I'D LIKE
TO GO TALK TO HIM.

04:50.507 --> 04:51.943
WOULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR
AND PACK UP THE GEAR?

04:52.074 --> 04:52.988
-ALEX: SURE.

04:59.299 --> 05:01.388
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

05:03.215 --> 05:04.565
I WAS WONDERING.

05:05.348 --> 05:08.482
CAN YOU MAKE YOUR FOOTPRINTS
DISAPPEAR IN THE SAND?

05:09.657 --> 05:10.832
I CAN.

05:12.224 --> 05:13.530
COME ON, I'LL SHOW YOU.

05:13.661 --> 05:14.879
COME ON, COME ON.

05:16.881 --> 05:18.622
SO YOU'RE ALL READY FOR
YOUR BIG OUTRIGGER RACE?

05:18.753 --> 05:19.797
OH YEAH.

05:19.928 --> 05:21.321
HEY, THANKS FOR
GIVING ME THE TIME OFF.

05:21.451 --> 05:22.887
-I OWE YOU ONE.
-YEAH, YOU GOT IT.

05:23.018 --> 05:24.933
YOU KNOW, YOU MAY EVEN SEE
TIMMY AND MY SISTER OVER THERE.

05:25.063 --> 05:26.369
THEY'RE GONNA BE
ON THE BIG ISLAND TOO.

05:26.500 --> 05:27.457
-THAT'D BE GREAT.
-YEAH.

05:27.588 --> 05:29.633
-OKAY, FOLLOW ME, FOLLOW ME.

05:29.764 --> 05:30.895
OKAY NOW,

05:31.026 --> 05:33.028
TAKE YOUR FEET,
PUT THEM IN THE SAND.

05:34.203 --> 05:37.598
LIKE THIS, STEP BACK, WATCH.

05:40.992 --> 05:42.864
AND THERE YOU GO, SEE,
MAGIC, THEY'RE GONE.

05:42.994 --> 05:44.256
SEE THAT?

05:45.040 --> 05:45.780
YOU WANNA TRY IT?

05:45.910 --> 05:47.477
C'MON.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.087
ATTABOY.

05:50.959 --> 05:52.264
GO AHEAD.

05:52.395 --> 05:54.745
ALL RIGHT,
GET THEM IN THERE GOOD.

05:55.267 --> 05:57.661
BACK UP A LITTLE BIT, OKAY.

05:59.228 --> 06:00.534
[TIMMY SCREAMS]

06:01.752 --> 06:04.407
HEY, HEY, HEY,
COME HERE, COME HERE, COME HERE.

06:04.973 --> 06:07.671
-IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY,
TAKE IT EASY, KID.

06:08.063 --> 06:10.370
TIMMY IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

06:11.501 --> 06:14.286
-IT'S OKAY, IT'S ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT, IT'S EASY.

06:14.417 --> 06:17.115
-ALEX: TIMMY, TIMMY, TIMMY,
CALM DOWN, SWEETIE, IT'S OKAY.

06:17.246 --> 06:19.030
HE HATES TO GET SPLASHED
WITH THE WATER.

06:19.640 --> 06:22.164
IT'S ALL RIGHT,
SWEETIE, YOU OKAY?

06:36.613 --> 06:38.572
-WHAT'S HE DOING?
-HE'S LOOKING AT THE DOLPHINS.

06:48.799 --> 06:50.497
HE ABSOLUTELY LOVES DOLPHINS.

06:50.627 --> 06:52.412
THAT'S WHY THEY'RE
GONNA GO TO HAWAII.

06:52.542 --> 06:54.631
THERE'S THIS PLACE,
IT'S CALLED DOLPHIN QUEST.

06:54.762 --> 06:56.981
-YEAH, I WAS THERE A
COUPLE YEARS AGO WITH HOBIE.

06:57.112 --> 06:58.896
PRETTY INCREDIBLE.

06:59.027 --> 07:01.072
IS IT TRUE YOU ACTUALLY
CAN GET IN THE WATER WITH THEM?

07:01.203 --> 07:02.900
YEAH, YEAH,
YOU SWIM WITH THEM,

07:03.292 --> 07:04.989
TOUCH THEM, INTERACT,
IT'S GREAT.

07:05.120 --> 07:07.470
TIMOTHY IS IN FOR
THE TIME OF HIS LIFE.

07:21.789 --> 07:24.400
-ALEX: WOO HOO!
LOOK AT THOSE BUTTS!

07:24.531 --> 07:25.706
-MITCH: GOOD MORNING, ALEX.

07:25.836 --> 07:27.185
-ALEX: GOOD MORNING, GUYS.

07:27.316 --> 07:29.274
-SHOULD HAVE HAD YOUR NEPHEW
OUT THERE WITH US TODAY.

07:29.405 --> 07:30.624
-YOU MISSED IT.

07:30.754 --> 07:32.974
DOLPHINS WENT RIGHT BY US
FOR TWO MILES.

07:34.192 --> 07:35.237
A THING OF BEAUTY.

07:35.367 --> 07:36.847
TIMMY WOULD HAVE LOVED THAT.

07:37.152 --> 07:39.110
WHEN ARE WE GONNA GET YOU
ON A PADDLEBOARD?

07:39.241 --> 07:41.069
SOON, VERY SOON.

07:44.115 --> 07:46.248
HEY, IT'S MY SISTER!

07:46.378 --> 07:47.554
-VALERIE!

07:51.035 --> 07:52.472
-VALERIE, HI.

07:54.038 --> 07:56.040
HEY, THIS IS MITCH,
THIS IS CODY.

07:56.171 --> 07:57.085
-MORNING.
-HI.

07:57.215 --> 07:58.869
-HI.
-HI.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.915
SO WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE HOME PACKING.

08:01.045 --> 08:02.960
-YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE THIS.
-WHAT?

08:03.308 --> 08:05.833
MY BOSS JUST DROPPED
THIS HUGE PROJECT IN MY LAP.

08:05.963 --> 08:07.530
THERE'S NO WAY I CAN GET AWAY
FOR THE WEEKEND.

08:07.661 --> 08:09.227
IT LOOKS LIKE
HAWAII IS OUT.

08:09.358 --> 08:10.620
I'M SORRY.

08:11.055 --> 08:12.840
I KNOW TIMMY IS GONNA BE
SO DISAPPOINTED.

08:12.970 --> 08:16.800
I KNOW, HE HAS HAD HIS HEART
SET ON SEEING THOSE DOLPHINS.

08:16.931 --> 08:19.760
I'VE BEEN SHOWING HIM PICTURES
OF THE HOTEL FOR MONTHS.

08:19.890 --> 08:22.023
WHAT ABOUT AUNT ALEX?

08:22.371 --> 08:23.764
WHAT ABOUT AUNT ALEX?

08:23.894 --> 08:25.374
WHY CAN'T YOU TAKE HIM?

08:25.505 --> 08:27.202
OH, I COULDN'T ASK HER
TO DO THAT.

08:27.332 --> 08:29.117
YOU DIDN'T. I DID.

08:29.247 --> 08:30.161
MITCH...

08:30.292 --> 08:31.423
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

08:31.989 --> 08:32.903
HEY, I'LL BE THERE,
I CAN HELP YOU OUT.

08:33.817 --> 08:34.905
WHERE YOU STAYING?

08:35.035 --> 08:36.472
WE'VE GOT A SUITE
AT THE HILTON WAIKOLOA

08:37.038 --> 08:38.518
AND TWO TICKETS
ON HAWAIIAN AIRLINES.

08:38.648 --> 08:40.041
IT'S ALL BEEN PAID FOR.

08:40.607 --> 08:41.650
[MITCH AND CODY] SHE'S IN.

08:41.782 --> 08:42.913
WILL YOU STOP?

08:43.044 --> 08:44.567
BOTH OF YOU GUYS!

08:45.046 --> 08:47.135
LOOK, VALERIE, I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN HANDLE THIS.

08:47.265 --> 08:48.876
I MEAN, I KNOW I CAN'T
TAKE THE TIME OFF OF WORK

08:49.006 --> 08:50.791
AND THIS PLACE IS SO
DISORGANIZED.

08:50.921 --> 08:52.183
-EXCUSE ME, EXCUSE US,

08:52.314 --> 08:53.837
WOULD YOU STEP INTO MY OFFICE
FOR A MINUTE?

08:55.012 --> 08:57.014
I KNOW I HAVE NO BUSINESS
TELLING YOU THIS,

08:57.145 --> 08:58.407
I'M PROBABLY WAY OUT OF LINE,
BUT...

08:58.538 --> 08:59.669
BUT YOU'RE GONNA DO IT ANYWAY.

08:59.800 --> 09:02.150
-BUT, AS MUCH AS WE APPRECIATE

09:02.280 --> 09:04.108
YOUR CONTRIBUTION
HERE AT BAYWATCH,

09:04.848 --> 09:07.111
THIS LITTLE BOY NEEDS YOU
A LOT MORE THAN WE DO.

09:09.853 --> 09:10.593
OKAY.

09:11.159 --> 09:12.116
[ALEX GROANS]

09:12.247 --> 09:13.640
-OKAY I'M IN.
-MITCH: SHE'S IN.

09:13.770 --> 09:15.206
-ATTAGIRL!
-YOU SURE?

09:15.337 --> 09:16.860
YEAH, I'M POSITIVE,
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

09:16.991 --> 09:19.123
OH, THANK YOU, AL.

09:19.471 --> 09:21.125
YOU'RE WELCOME, VALERIE.

09:21.256 --> 09:22.431
-STEWARDESS: ALOHA.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.302
-ON BEHALF OF ALL OF US
AT HAWAIIAN AIRLINES,

09:24.433 --> 09:26.696
WE WANT TO THANK YOU FOR
CHOOSING TO FLY WITH US TODAY.

09:27.218 --> 09:29.351
-WELCOME TO HAWAII. MAHALO.

09:30.482 --> 09:33.442
-ALEX: OH MY GOD, LOOK AT
THIS PLACE, IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

09:47.151 --> 09:48.152
-CODY: SWEET DIGS, HUH?

09:48.283 --> 09:50.807
-ALEX: WOW, THIS PLACE
IS AMAZING, HUH?

09:50.938 --> 09:52.287
-CODY: AREN'T YOU GLAD
YOU CAME?

10:13.961 --> 10:15.484
-ALEX: WILL YOU LOOK AT HIM?

10:16.485 --> 10:18.313
-CODY: WHAT'S HE GONNA DO
WHEN HE SEES THE REAL THING?

10:18.443 --> 10:19.880
-ALEX: THAT'S WHAT
I'M WONDERING.

10:20.445 --> 10:22.360
-CODY: HAVE YOU HEARD
OF DOLPHIN THERAPY?

10:23.274 --> 10:24.928
-I WAS READING ABOUT
IT ON THE PLANE.

10:25.276 --> 10:26.887
THERE'S THIS PLACE IN FLORIDA
THAT TREATS KIDS

10:27.017 --> 10:28.715
-WITH DISABILITIES.
-LOOK, CODY...

10:29.324 --> 10:30.804
DON'T GET YOUR HOPES UP, OKAY?

10:31.543 --> 10:33.763
-WELL, THERE'S ALWAYS A CHANCE.
-NO, THERE'S NOT.

10:34.329 --> 10:36.026
THERE IS NO CURE FOR AUTISM.

10:36.853 --> 10:39.639
WE CAME HERE ON VACATION,
NOT IN SEARCH OF A MIRACLE.

10:41.379 --> 10:42.859
TIMMY CAME HERE WITH AUTISM

10:42.990 --> 10:44.861
AND HE'S GONNA
LEAVE WITH AUTISM.

10:45.732 --> 10:48.082
AND UNFORTUNATELY,
NOTHING IS GONNA CHANGE THAT.

10:49.953 --> 10:51.607
[SOFT MUSIC]

11:11.018 --> 11:12.541
[WATER SKI ENGINE]

11:30.167 --> 11:31.603
CODY!

11:34.606 --> 11:36.173
YOU DON'T REMEMBER ME, DO YOU?

11:36.304 --> 11:37.914
KALI MCKENZIE?

11:38.045 --> 11:39.046
LANI'S SISTER?

11:39.611 --> 11:41.178
I MET YOU LAST SUMMER
WHEN I WAS IN LA.

11:41.309 --> 11:43.441
OH, RIGHT, RIGHT,
I'M SORRY.

11:43.790 --> 11:45.617
-NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.
-SAME HERE.

11:46.227 --> 11:47.576
SO HAVE YOU TALKED
TO LANI LATELY?

11:48.142 --> 11:49.621
NOT SINCE SHE
MOVED TO NEW YORK.

11:49.883 --> 11:51.058
HOW IS SHE DOING?

11:51.362 --> 11:53.800
GOOD, I GUESS, WE HAVEN'T
REALLY TALKED MUCH EITHER.

11:54.626 --> 11:57.238
NOT SURE WE'RE CUT OUT FOR
A BI-COASTAL RELATIONSHIP.

11:57.368 --> 11:59.066
OH, SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

11:59.196 --> 12:01.285
IT'S NOT LIKE WE'RE
OFFICIALLY SPLIT UP.

12:02.330 --> 12:03.505
WE'RE JUST NOT TOGETHER.

12:04.071 --> 12:04.854
SO WHERE YOU STAYING?

12:04.985 --> 12:06.595
THE HILTON WAIKOLOA,

12:06.726 --> 12:08.075
I'M HERE
FOR THAT OUTRIGGER RACE.

12:08.379 --> 12:11.513
OH NO, THE RACE JUST GOT
POSTPONED TILL NEXT WEEK.

12:11.643 --> 12:13.341
HMM, YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME.

12:13.471 --> 12:14.864
NO, THERE'S A
BIG STORM COMING.

12:14.995 --> 12:17.258
THEY THOUGHT THE SQUALLS
MIGHT AFFECT THE RACE.

12:18.085 --> 12:19.956
YOU MEAN, I CAME
ALL THE WAY HERE FOR NOTHING.

12:21.262 --> 12:22.698
HOPEFULLY YOU'LL FIND
SOMETHING ELSE

12:22.829 --> 12:24.352
TO MAKE YOUR TRIP INTERESTING.

12:30.314 --> 12:31.228
[TIMMY SQUEALS]

12:32.055 --> 12:34.492
TIMMY, IF YOU WANT
TO SWIM WITH THE DOLPHINS,

12:34.623 --> 12:35.885
YOU NEED TO PUT
YOUR VEST ON.

12:36.016 --> 12:39.236
LOOK, ALL THE OTHER KIDS
ARE PUTTING VESTS ON, SEE?

12:39.367 --> 12:40.498
-MORNING, SORRY I'M LATE.

12:41.108 --> 12:42.196
WHERE YOU BEEN?

12:42.326 --> 12:43.763
OH, IT'S A LONG STORY.

12:43.893 --> 12:46.200
BOTTOM LINE IS,
I'M NOT GONNA BE RACING.

12:46.330 --> 12:47.679
WHY NOT?

12:48.071 --> 12:49.029
I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.728
HEY, TIMMY, WANT SOME HELP
PUTTING ON YOUR VEST, BUDDY?

12:53.555 --> 12:54.599
HUH?

12:55.122 --> 12:56.471
WHAT DO YOU SAY,
WE'LL PUT YOUR VEST ON,

12:56.601 --> 12:59.691
WE'LL GO SEE THE DOLPHINS,
WHAT DO YOU THINK, YEAH?

12:59.822 --> 13:00.780
[ALEX GROANS]

13:01.824 --> 13:02.869
WELCOME TO DOLPHIN QUEST.

13:02.999 --> 13:05.001
MY NAME IS JO
AND THIS IS TAMMY.

13:05.132 --> 13:06.524
LET'S MEET OUR
DOLPHIN FRIENDS TODAY.

13:07.090 --> 13:09.092
THEIR NAMES ARE
LOLO, PELE AND KONA.

13:09.223 --> 13:10.790
KONA IS PREGNANT
AND EXPECTING ANY DAY.

13:15.969 --> 13:17.405
[WILDLIFE SOUNDS]

13:24.455 --> 13:26.980
IT'S NO USE, I DON'T THINK
HE WANTS TO GO IN THE WATER.

13:28.720 --> 13:30.766
GIVE IT SOME TIME,
LET HIM GET USED TO BEING HERE.

13:31.549 --> 13:32.724
HE'LL DO IT.

13:33.900 --> 13:36.250
I'M GONNA GO GET HIM
AN ICE CREAM.

13:37.294 --> 13:39.209
-ALL RIGHT, WE'LL SIT HERE
AND WATCH THE DOLPHINS.

13:39.862 --> 13:40.820
[SOFT MUSIC]

13:45.172 --> 13:47.348
♪ LIFE

13:49.654 --> 13:52.788
♪ SO DIVINE

13:56.357 --> 13:58.359
♪ TIME

14:01.144 --> 14:04.147
♪ WON'T REWIND

14:09.544 --> 14:15.550
♪ HAVE NO FEAR
WHEN WE'RE APART ♪

14:20.816 --> 14:26.822
♪ YOU CAN FEEL IT
IN YOUR HEART ♪

14:32.219 --> 14:34.395
♪ WE ARE ONE

14:34.525 --> 14:40.531
♪ WE'RE ALL THE SAME

14:43.621 --> 14:45.623
♪ WE ARE ONE

14:45.754 --> 14:51.803
♪ WHEN LOVE REMAINS

14:54.632 --> 14:56.678
♪ WE ARE ONE

14:57.244 --> 15:03.076
♪ WITH NATURE'S GLEAM ♪

15:05.992 --> 15:08.124
♪ WE ARE ONE

15:08.255 --> 15:14.261
♪ WITH EVERYTHING

15:14.565 --> 15:16.393
♪ OHHH ♪

15:24.401 --> 15:28.449
♪ WE ARE WE ARE WE ARE

15:36.674 --> 15:38.024
-LET'S REVIEW
WHAT WE'VE LEARNED TODAY.

15:38.154 --> 15:39.590
HOW MANY TEETH
DO DOLPHINS HAVE?

15:39.721 --> 15:41.157
KIDS: EIGHTY EIGHT.

15:41.288 --> 15:43.855
-WHY ARE PLASTIC RING TABS
DANGEROUS FOR THE DOLPHINS?

15:43.986 --> 15:45.770
KIDS: THEY MIGHT GET
CAUGHT ON THEIR MOUTH.

15:45.901 --> 15:47.859
WHY ARE BALLOONS
DANGEROUS IN THE WATER?

15:47.990 --> 15:50.601
KIDS: THEY MIGHT GET
CAUGHT IN THEIR THROAT.

15:50.732 --> 15:53.126
WHO IS THE BIGGEST
ENEMY TO THE DOLPHINS,

15:53.256 --> 15:55.302
SHARKS, ORCAS OR HUMANS?

15:55.432 --> 15:57.434
-HUMANS.
-WHAT CAN WE DO TO CHANGE THIS?

15:57.565 --> 15:59.088
RECYCLE!

15:59.871 --> 16:00.916
GOOD.

16:01.047 --> 16:02.439
[DOLPHIN NOISE]

16:06.356 --> 16:07.705
[KIDS CHATTING]

16:12.928 --> 16:14.277
[WILDLIFE NOISE]

16:35.168 --> 16:36.865
HEY THERE, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

16:40.173 --> 16:41.304
YOU LIKE DOLPHINS?

16:42.523 --> 16:43.959
YOU WANNA GIVE IT A TRY?

16:50.313 --> 16:51.488
GREAT.

16:54.535 --> 16:56.015
A MAMA AND HER BABY.

16:58.974 --> 17:00.149
-ALEX: CODY!

17:03.500 --> 17:04.022
WHERE'S TIMMY?

17:05.720 --> 17:06.676
HE WAS HERE
JUST TWO MINUTES AGO.

17:07.852 --> 17:09.115
-ALEX: TIMMY?

17:10.290 --> 17:11.551
TIMMY?

17:18.211 --> 17:21.431
TIMMY,
YOU SCARED ME HALF TO DEATH.

17:22.084 --> 17:24.565
SORRY ABOUT THAT,
HOPE HE'S NOT INTERRUPTING YOU.

17:24.694 --> 17:27.959
NOT AT ALL, I THINK WE SHARE
A COMMON LOVE OF DOLPHINS.

17:29.178 --> 17:30.571
I'M ALEX, THIS IS CODY.

17:30.701 --> 17:31.485
NICE TO MEET YOU.

17:31.615 --> 17:32.660
MY NAME IS WYLAND.

17:32.790 --> 17:33.791
NICE TO MEET YOU.

17:33.922 --> 17:36.011
AND THIS IS TIMMY.

17:36.533 --> 17:38.057
HE'S AUTISTIC, HE DOESN'T SPEAK.

17:39.667 --> 17:42.626
SOMETIMES YOU DON'T HAVE
TO SPEAK TO BE UNDERSTOOD.

17:43.714 --> 17:45.194
NICE TO MEET YOU, TIMMY.

17:59.817 --> 18:01.819
THAT'S WHERE THE RACE
WAS SUPPOSED TO START.

18:01.950 --> 18:03.386
-REALLY?
-YEAH.

18:03.908 --> 18:05.606
I THINK TIMMY'S
HAVING A GOOD TIME, HUH?

18:09.871 --> 18:10.654
HEY, KALI!

18:12.221 --> 18:13.744
-CODY: HANG ON A SEC.
-OKAY.

18:14.223 --> 18:16.443
SWEETIE YOU SIT RIGHT HERE,
C'MON, C'MON.

18:18.314 --> 18:20.011
THERE YOU GO,
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK, OKAY?

18:23.450 --> 18:24.799
KALI, WHAT'S UP?

18:24.929 --> 18:26.801
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

18:27.497 --> 18:29.456
ALEX, THIS IS KALI MCKENZIE.

18:29.586 --> 18:31.284
-HI. NICE TO MEET YOU.
-YOU TOO.

18:31.414 --> 18:33.155
KALI'S SISTER
USED TO WORK AT BAYWATCH.

18:33.416 --> 18:34.983
LANI MCKENZIE, RIGHT?

18:35.114 --> 18:36.332
SO WHAT'S UP,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:36.463 --> 18:38.291
WELL, I TALKED TO LANI
LAST NIGHT

18:38.421 --> 18:40.119
AND SHE SAID YOU'D BE BUMMED
ABOUT NOT BEING IN THE RACE

18:40.249 --> 18:42.599
AND THAT I SHOULD TAKE YOU OUT
FOR A TOUR OF THE ISLAND.

18:43.600 --> 18:44.775
BUT IF YOU HAVE OTHER PLANS...

18:46.037 --> 18:47.952
NO, GO ON.

18:48.518 --> 18:49.345
YOU'RE SURE?

18:49.737 --> 18:50.955
I THINK I CAN MANAGE.

18:51.521 --> 18:53.828
BESIDES THIS MAY BE YOUR ONLY
CHANCE TO GET IN AN OUTRIGGER.

18:54.698 --> 18:56.047
-THANK YOU.
-SURE.

18:56.613 --> 18:58.441
ALL RIGHT,
CATCH YOU LATER, TIMMY!

18:58.572 --> 18:59.573
-ALEX: HAVE A GOOD TIME.

18:59.703 --> 19:00.922
KALI:] I'LL HAVE
HIM BACK BY DINNER.

19:01.836 --> 19:05.144
I BROUGHT THIS...
FOR YOU.

19:08.190 --> 19:10.627
THANK YOU, IT SMELLS GREAT.

19:11.280 --> 19:12.368
-LET'S GO.

19:12.977 --> 19:14.196
[ADVENTURE MUSIC]

19:31.866 --> 19:35.043
ALEX: I PROMISE, VAL, YES.

19:35.174 --> 19:37.698
WE ARE IN ONE OF THE MOST
PEACEFUL SETTINGS IN THE WORLD,

19:37.828 --> 19:39.221
HOW CAN IT NOT BE GOING GREAT?

19:39.961 --> 19:41.963
DON'T YOU THINK I WOULD
TELL YOU IF WASN'T WORKING OUT?

19:42.093 --> 19:43.530
HE'S HAPPY AS A CLAM.

19:45.053 --> 19:46.794
YES, YOU KNOW WHAT,
ABSOLUTELY.

19:46.924 --> 19:48.012
I WILL CALL YOU
FIRST THING TOMORROW.

19:48.143 --> 19:49.362
ALL RIGHT, BYE.

19:51.451 --> 19:54.628
[SCREAMS]

19:54.758 --> 19:56.195
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
IT'S OKAY.

19:56.325 --> 19:58.414
IT'S OKAY, C'MON, C'MON.

19:59.459 --> 20:01.896
TIMMY, IT'S OKAY,
SSH, IT'S OKAY.

20:02.026 --> 20:03.245
IT'S OKAY.

20:03.376 --> 20:04.681
YOU DROPPED YOUR GLASS?

20:04.812 --> 20:06.857
TIMMY CALM DOWN,
SHH, IT'S OKAY.

20:06.988 --> 20:08.294
YOU KNOW WHAT,
WE'LL GO GET IT, OKAY?

20:08.424 --> 20:10.209
YOU WANNA GO GET YOUR GLASS,
BABY?

20:10.557 --> 20:11.906
IT'S OKAY.

20:12.036 --> 20:13.516
[SQUEALS]

20:13.647 --> 20:15.344
COME ON, LET'S GO GET YOUR
GLASS, WE'LL GET IT TOGETHER.

20:15.475 --> 20:16.954
[CRIES]

20:17.085 --> 20:18.391
I KNOW, COME ON,
LET'S GO THIS WAY.

20:18.521 --> 20:19.957
WE'LL GO GET YOUR GLASS.

20:24.571 --> 20:25.659
[CRIES]

20:36.235 --> 20:38.585
TIMMY LOOK,
I GOT YOUR GLASS, SWEETIE.

20:38.715 --> 20:39.716
[CRIES]

20:41.109 --> 20:42.719
HERE YOU GO,
HERE YOU GO.

20:43.154 --> 20:45.069
IT'S OKAY, SHH...

20:46.462 --> 20:48.247
IT'S OKAY, SSH, CALM DOWN.

20:49.422 --> 20:50.771
CALM DOWN.

20:53.426 --> 20:54.644
IT'S OKAY.

21:04.915 --> 21:06.526
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

21:18.799 --> 21:19.930
HOW'S TIMMY?

21:21.062 --> 21:22.716
WELL, HE'S FINE AT THE MOMENT.

21:22.846 --> 21:24.805
I, ON THE OTHER HAND,
AM A NERVOUS WRECK.

21:25.675 --> 21:27.416
I CAN IMAGINE
IT CAN BE FRUSTRATING.

21:27.547 --> 21:28.504
YEAH.

21:28.635 --> 21:30.680
WOW, A PUZZLE WITH NO PICTURE.

21:31.246 --> 21:32.595
HE LIKES TO PUT THEM
TOGETHER UPSIDE DOWN.

21:32.726 --> 21:34.205
THAT WAY IT'S MORE CHALLENGING.

21:34.641 --> 21:35.816
AMAZING.

21:35.946 --> 21:37.426
TIMMY, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SEE MY DRAWING?

21:37.557 --> 21:38.688
IT'S ALMOST FINISHED.

21:38.819 --> 21:40.037
OH, WOW!

21:40.603 --> 21:42.997
THAT'S GREAT, YEAH!

21:44.868 --> 21:47.262
WELL, TIMMY, I SHOWED YOU
MY DRAWING, LET ME SEE YOURS.

22:01.755 --> 22:03.234
KALI: LANI SAID
YOU WERE GOING TO NEW YORK

22:03.365 --> 22:04.975
AND YOUR PLANE CRASHED?

22:05.585 --> 22:06.760
YEP.

22:06.890 --> 22:08.239
WHAT WAS THAT LIKE?

22:08.588 --> 22:10.503
LET'S JUST SAY
IT WAS PRETTY INTENSE.

22:10.807 --> 22:13.593
AND YOU HAD NO PROBLEM GETTING
ON A PLANE AND FLYING AGAIN?

22:14.158 --> 22:15.290
I FIGURED, YOU KNOW,

22:15.421 --> 22:16.726
WHAT ARE THE ODDS
OF IT HAPPENING TWICE?

22:17.074 --> 22:18.075
A TRILLION TO ONE?

22:19.163 --> 22:20.600
YOU KNOW,
SURVIVING SOMETHING LIKE THAT

22:20.730 --> 22:22.036
MAKES YOU KIND OF FEARLESS.

22:32.089 --> 22:34.004
YOU SEE THE HOLES
IN THOSE ROCKS?

22:36.398 --> 22:37.007
CODY: YEAH.

22:37.138 --> 22:38.400
THOSE ARE LAVA TUBES.

22:38.531 --> 22:40.359
THEY WERE FORMED
THOUSANDS OF YEARS AGO.

22:41.969 --> 22:43.753
HAWAIIANS BELIEVE
THIS AREA TO BE HAUNTED

22:43.884 --> 22:46.277
SINCE A LAVA TUBE
LOOKS LIKE AN EVIL SPIRIT.

22:46.582 --> 22:49.106
LEGEND HAS IT THAT YOU
REMOVE THE LAVA FROM THIS AREA,

22:49.237 --> 22:51.370
YOU'LL BE CURSED FOREVER.

22:52.458 --> 22:53.589
NO THANKS.

22:58.115 --> 23:00.030
KALI: THIS IS MY FIND.

23:00.161 --> 23:01.684
I CALL IT DRAGON'S THROAT.

23:01.815 --> 23:03.686
CODY: 'CAUSE IT LOOKS
LIKE A DRAGON'S THROAT?

23:03.817 --> 23:06.297
NO, I JUST LIKE THE SOUND OF IT.

23:27.014 --> 23:31.410
THIS IS MY FAVORITE SPOT
ON THE ISLAND, KEALAKEKUA.

23:32.062 --> 23:33.847
IT MEANS PATHWAY OF THE GODS.

23:34.195 --> 23:36.066
THEY FILMED THE OLD
SERIES "SEAHUNT" HERE.

23:36.197 --> 23:37.546
THAT WAS BEFORE MY TIME.

23:38.504 --> 23:40.070
READY FOR THE BEST PART
OF THE TOUR?

23:50.646 --> 23:52.561
[GENTLE MUSIC]

24:54.667 --> 24:56.799
[WASHES CRASH]

25:03.240 --> 25:06.374
-CHECK THIS OUT, MAN!
-YEAH, IT'S THE BOMB.

25:18.778 --> 25:20.301
HEY, BE CAREFUL, DUDE!

25:22.085 --> 25:23.522
[SCREAMS]

25:25.741 --> 25:27.308
[SCREAMS]

25:30.616 --> 25:31.791
[SCREAMS]

25:34.794 --> 25:36.012
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

25:41.757 --> 25:43.150
HELP!

25:48.764 --> 25:51.375
-WHAT'S UP, WHAT WAS THAT?
-HELP! MY FRIEND! HELP!

25:51.506 --> 25:53.552
-KALI: WHERE IS HE?
-HE FELL!

25:55.031 --> 25:56.990
HE GOT SWEPT INTO THE CAVE!

25:57.773 --> 25:58.992
[GASPS]

26:03.736 --> 26:05.564
HELP! HELP!

26:11.918 --> 26:13.267
HELP!

26:14.398 --> 26:15.791
HELP ME!

26:16.618 --> 26:17.576
[CHOKES]

26:18.533 --> 26:19.534
HELP!

26:26.149 --> 26:27.498
[CHOKES]

26:34.157 --> 26:35.550
CODY: HOW FAR BACK DOES IT GO?

26:35.681 --> 26:36.943
KALI: FORTY FEET.

26:50.609 --> 26:51.610
AARGH!

26:53.437 --> 26:56.005
-CODY: I DON'T SEE HIM, DO YOU?
-KALI: NO!

27:04.318 --> 27:05.972
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

27:19.333 --> 27:21.640
CODY, I'VE GOT HIM,
I NEED HELP!

27:23.119 --> 27:24.643
CODY: HANG ON, HANG ON!

27:26.993 --> 27:28.298
I'VE GOT HIM, I'VE GOT HIM.

27:28.429 --> 27:29.822
LET'S GO, LET'S GET OUT!

27:40.833 --> 27:42.356
[MUSIC SLOWS]

27:55.456 --> 27:56.500
CODY: CALL THE LIFEGUARDS!

27:56.631 --> 27:58.111
TELL THEM
WE'RE BRINGING IN A VICTIM!

28:04.770 --> 28:05.945
-LOOK, TIMMY, LOOK.

28:07.207 --> 28:08.077
WOW!

28:10.036 --> 28:11.646
[TENSE MUSIC]

28:16.956 --> 28:18.653
TIMMY, I WANT YOU TO
STAY RIGHT HERE, OKAY?

28:18.958 --> 28:21.090
DON'T GET UP, SWEETIE,
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

28:26.313 --> 28:28.924
GET THAT BACKBOARD IN HERE,
POSSIBLE NECK INJURY!

28:38.281 --> 28:39.543
[TIMMY GROANS]

28:49.640 --> 28:50.772
-HE'S IN.

28:51.338 --> 28:53.296
CODY: OKAY LET'S LIFT
ON THREE, READY?

28:53.427 --> 28:56.038
ONE, TWO, THREE: LIFT.

28:56.169 --> 28:57.344
ALEX: CODY, WHAT HAPPENED?

28:57.474 --> 28:59.302
GUY FELL OFF A CLIFF,
POSSIBLE NECK INJURY.

29:02.523 --> 29:03.959
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

29:06.919 --> 29:08.355
CODY: CAREFUL LOADING HIM
IN IT.

29:14.753 --> 29:16.058
CODY: EASY NOW, EASY.

30:04.411 --> 30:06.369
-I'M GONNA GO WITH THEM.
-ALL RIGHT, HE'S ALL YOURS.

30:07.109 --> 30:08.502
-YOU ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH.

30:09.720 --> 30:11.244
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

30:14.377 --> 30:15.683
TIMMY'S GONE.

30:17.206 --> 30:18.338
TIMMY?

31:17.701 --> 31:19.225
TIMMY!

31:22.010 --> 31:23.838
GOOD JOB, TIMMY. LET ME TAKE
A LOOK AT HER, BUDDY.

31:23.969 --> 31:24.883
GOOD JOB.

31:28.974 --> 31:31.237
NO PULSE, STILL NOT BREATHING,
CONTINUE CPR.

31:36.329 --> 31:39.898
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE:

31:40.028 --> 31:41.116
BREATHE.

31:42.683 --> 31:46.208
ONE , TWO , THREE, FOUR, FIVE:
BREATHE.

31:48.080 --> 31:51.779
ONE, TWO THREE, FOUR FIVE:
BREATHE.

31:52.823 --> 31:53.912
[COUGHS]

31:54.042 --> 31:55.391
-ATTAGIRL, ATTAGIRL.
-THERE YOU GO!

31:55.522 --> 31:58.699
-MOTHER: MALEA, MALEA,
MALEA, MALEA!

31:58.829 --> 32:00.309
OH, WHAT HAPPENED TO MY BABY?

32:00.440 --> 32:02.659
-SHE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
-YOU OKAY?

32:06.359 --> 32:08.491
HEY, WILL YOU TAKE HER UP
AND CHECK HER VITALS?

32:08.622 --> 32:09.579
-YEAH.
-THANKS, MAN.

32:09.710 --> 32:11.146
HER PULSE IS GOOD.

32:12.060 --> 32:13.932
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR SAVING MY BABY.

32:14.062 --> 32:15.498
YOU'RE WELCOME.

32:23.898 --> 32:25.465
WAY TO GO, TIMMY!

32:25.769 --> 32:27.336
HOW DID YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO?

32:27.815 --> 32:29.643
HE SAW US
PERFORM CPR ON THE BEACH.

32:29.773 --> 32:31.514
HE REMEMBERED EVERY MOVE.

32:31.645 --> 32:33.690
ALEX: LOOK AT YOU,
YOU'RE SOAKING WET.

32:34.126 --> 32:37.172
YOU WENT IN THE WATER AND YOU
WEREN'T EVEN AFRAID, WERE YOU?

32:39.783 --> 32:41.307
SEE, TOLD YOU HE'D DO IT.

32:41.916 --> 32:43.091
HE JUST WANTED TO PICK HIS SPOT.

32:46.790 --> 32:48.270
WAY TO GO, KIDDO.

32:49.532 --> 32:50.751
[GROANS]

32:53.972 --> 32:56.975
♪ YOU DON'T HAVE TO
SAY A WORD ♪

32:59.847 --> 33:02.937
♪ OR HOW I SEE YOU

33:04.504 --> 33:08.595
♪ JUST TAKE ONE STEP FORWARD

33:09.857 --> 33:13.556
♪ INTO OCEANS BRAND NEW

33:15.254 --> 33:18.997
♪ REACH INSIDE
IT'S TIME TO BE BRAVE ♪

33:19.127 --> 33:23.262
♪ THERE'S NO TIME
TO BE AFRAID ♪

33:25.786 --> 33:29.529
♪ YOU'VE GOT NOTHING TO FEAR

33:29.659 --> 33:33.968
♪ AND JUST KNOW
I'LL ALWAYS BE HERE ♪

33:34.099 --> 33:37.015
♪ TO WATCH YOU SOAR

33:38.059 --> 33:40.235
♪ OVER MOUNTAINS SO HIGH

33:40.366 --> 33:42.498
♪ WATCH YOU SOAR

33:42.803 --> 33:45.371
♪ SEE YOU TOUCHING THE SKY ♪

33:45.501 --> 33:47.895
♪ WATCH YOU SOAR

33:48.896 --> 33:52.682
♪ FLY THORUGH THAT OPEN DOOR

33:55.250 --> 33:57.861
♪ I'LL WATCH YOU SOAR

34:16.880 --> 34:19.882
♪ I'LL WATCH YOU SOAR

34:20.580 --> 34:22.712
♪ OVER MOUNTAINS SO HIGH ♪

34:23.016 --> 34:25.150
♪ WATCH YOU SOAR ♪

34:25.367 --> 34:28.152
♪ SEE YOU TOUCHING THE SKY ♪

34:28.283 --> 34:31.069
♪WATCH YOU SOAR

34:31.199 --> 34:35.899
♪ AND FLY
THROUGH THAT OPEN DOOR ♪

34:37.945 --> 34:40.556
♪ I'LL WATCH YOU SOAR

34:43.297 --> 34:46.388
♪ I'LL WATCH YOU SOAR

34:48.216 --> 34:52.264
♪ I'LL WATCH YOU SOAR

34:57.007 --> 34:58.444
-CODY: SO IT'S BEEN WORTH IT?

34:58.574 --> 34:59.967
ABSOLUTELY.

35:00.272 --> 35:01.795
THANK YOU.

35:02.883 --> 35:03.927
WE EVEN NOW?

35:04.624 --> 35:07.105
I THINK I MAY EVEN
OWE YOU A LITTLE.

35:07.540 --> 35:08.628
[ALEX CHUCKLES]

35:09.281 --> 35:10.456
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

35:10.586 --> 35:12.022
-YOU GOT IN THE WATER,
-THAT'S RIGHT.

35:12.153 --> 35:15.200
TOUCHED A DOLPHIN, YOU SAVED
A LITTLE GIRL'S LIFE, HUH?

35:17.202 --> 35:19.291
YES, MY MAN!

35:19.421 --> 35:21.815
HEY GUYS,
I HEAR TIMMY GOT IN THE WATER.

35:21.945 --> 35:24.818
HI. WELL YEAH, IT WAS TOUCH
AND GO THERE FOR A WHILE

35:24.948 --> 35:26.211
BUT WE ACCOMPLISHED
OUR MISSION.

35:26.776 --> 35:28.909
TIMMY SWAM WITH THE DOLPHINS.

35:29.039 --> 35:30.389
-ARTIST: WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.

35:30.519 --> 35:31.738
I HAVE SOMETHING FOR YOU.

35:32.565 --> 35:35.263
SOMETHING TO REMEMBER YOUR
TRIP TO THE HILTON WAIKOLOA.

35:35.394 --> 35:37.396
A PAINTING...
OF DOLPHINS.

35:37.526 --> 35:38.832
[GASPS]

35:40.181 --> 35:41.530
-ALEX: WHAT?

35:41.661 --> 35:43.402
-ARTIST: A MOMMY AND HER BABY.

35:44.403 --> 35:45.708
-ALEX: IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

35:47.493 --> 35:48.363
WOW.

35:50.060 --> 35:52.237
I KNOW HE WOULD SAY THANK YOU
IF HE COULD.

35:55.762 --> 35:56.893
HE DID.

36:00.375 --> 36:02.421
[SOFT MUSIC]

36:04.858 --> 36:07.077
[OCEAN SOUNDS]

36:19.133 --> 36:21.004
-CODY: SO THE KID
WAS ALL RIGHT, HUH?

36:21.135 --> 36:24.182
BRUISED RIBS, SLIGHT CONCUSSION,
NOTHING MAJOR.

36:24.312 --> 36:25.487
THAT'S ALWAYS GOOD TO HEAR.

36:26.140 --> 36:27.402
I NEVER GOT A CHANCE
TO THANK YOU

36:27.533 --> 36:28.969
FOR HELPING ME OUT
IN THE CAVE YESTERDAY.

36:29.099 --> 36:30.144
YOU'RE WELCOME.

36:33.103 --> 36:35.541
SO YOU PLANNING ANY TRIPS TO
THE MAINLAND IN THE NEAR FUTURE?

36:36.106 --> 36:39.719
I WASN'T BUT
YOU KNOW HOW THINGS CAN CHANGE.

36:40.720 --> 36:43.026
WELL, IF YOU DO, IT'LL BE
MY TURN TO SHOW YOU AROUND.

36:43.157 --> 36:44.506
YOU GOT A DEAL.

36:45.464 --> 36:46.726
I HOPE YOU AND LANI
CAN WORK THINGS OUT.

36:47.553 --> 36:48.815
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW.

36:50.164 --> 36:51.731
ANYTHING'S POSSIBLE,
I GUESS.

36:53.341 --> 36:55.256
[GENTLE MUSIC]

36:58.346 --> 37:00.653
I'LL TELL HER WHAT A FOOL
SHE'D BE TO LET YOU GO.

37:10.880 --> 37:12.055
HAVE A SAFE TRIP BACK.

37:13.535 --> 37:15.015
THANKS FOR PLAYING TOUR GUIDE.

37:25.939 --> 37:27.854
TIMMY, LOOK AT HIS EYES.

37:30.030 --> 37:31.945
THAT'S THE MOMMY DOLPHIN.

37:32.293 --> 37:33.338
ALOHA.

37:33.468 --> 37:34.382
ALOHA.

37:34.513 --> 37:35.992
-HOW YOU DOING?
-HEY.

37:36.123 --> 37:38.473
GOT YOU A FEW SOUVENIRS
YOU MIGHT LIKE, PAL.

37:38.604 --> 37:41.520
OH, THAT'S SWEET.

37:42.564 --> 37:43.826
CHECK THESE OUT.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.741
US AND THE MOMMY DOLPHINS,
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

37:45.872 --> 37:46.829
-CODY: THESE ARE CUTE!

37:47.656 --> 37:48.875
YOU'RE A PRETTY
GOOD PHOTOGRAPHER.

37:49.005 --> 37:50.050
WELL...

37:50.877 --> 37:52.357
I WAS HOPING YOU
HADN'T LEFT YET.

37:52.487 --> 37:54.576
THERE'S SOMETHING WE THINK TIMMY
MIGHT LIKE TO SEE. COME ON!

37:55.142 --> 37:56.143
LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

37:56.274 --> 37:57.753
C'MON, SWEETIE. LET'S GO.

37:58.319 --> 37:59.668
ALEX: LET'S GO.

38:03.368 --> 38:04.891
[DOLPHIN SOUNDS]

38:08.460 --> 38:10.462
[GENTLE MUSIC]

38:19.079 --> 38:21.864
[HAPPY MUSIC]

38:23.518 --> 38:25.912
-WOW!
-OH MAN! YEAH!

38:28.349 --> 38:30.482
[ADVENTURE MUSIC]

38:32.614 --> 38:33.746
[DOLPHIN SOUNDS]

38:40.927 --> 38:42.885
[DOLPHIN SOUNDS]

38:46.324 --> 38:47.760
AWESOME!

39:29.628 --> 39:31.194
MOMMY.

39:44.251 --> 39:45.948
-MOMMY.
-YES.

39:58.352 --> 39:59.745
ALEX: THANK YOU.
CODY: THANKS, MAN.

39:59.875 --> 40:01.007
-C'MON, SWEETIE, MOMMY'S HERE.

40:01.137 --> 40:03.226
MITCH: ALL RIGHT,
WHERE'S THE TROPHY?

40:03.705 --> 40:05.141
THERE WAS NO RACE.

40:05.272 --> 40:06.491
YOU MEAN YOU GOT
YOUR BUTT KICKED.

40:06.621 --> 40:07.622
NO, IT GOT POSTPONED.

40:07.753 --> 40:09.668
I SEE YOU MADE IT BACK
IN ONE PIECE.

40:09.798 --> 40:11.670
-YES. YOU ARE NOT GONNA
BELIEVE WHAT HAPPENED.

40:13.323 --> 40:15.282
DID YOU HAVE A GOOD TIME, TIMMY?

40:15.413 --> 40:16.718
-IT GOT POSTPONED.
-YEAH.

40:16.849 --> 40:18.720
WELL, WHAT'D YOU DO WITH
ALL YOUR TIME OVER THERE?

40:20.069 --> 40:22.115
FELL IN LOVE WITH LANI'S SISTER.

40:22.245 --> 40:24.378
-OH, I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

40:24.944 --> 40:26.206
-HEY.
-HI.

40:27.163 --> 40:28.208
[LAUGHING]

40:28.774 --> 40:31.864
WHAT DID YOU DO TO HIM,
I'VE NEVER SEEN HIM THIS HAPPY.

40:31.994 --> 40:34.606
HEY, TIMMY,
DON'T FORGET THIS BUDDY, HUH?

40:36.303 --> 40:40.307
WOW, WHERE DID YOU GET
SUCH A BEAUTIFUL PICTURE?

40:40.438 --> 40:42.091
